[0.005, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[24D\u001b[5B\r\u001b[10A\u001b[48;2;55;55;55m\u001b[38;2;80;80;80m❯ \u001b[38;2;255;255;255mWe implemented inbound-webhooks but we've learned that raw HTTP handlers won't scale. We need schema \u001b[39m      \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mvalidation on inbound payloads, dead-letter handling for events that fail processing, CloudEvents format for\u001b[39m \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255m standardization, and pluggable routing instead of hardcoded provider handlers. I've already sparke \u001b[39m         \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mevent-ingestion-pipeline as the replacement. Supersede inbound-webhooks with event-ingestion-pipeline and \u001b[39m   \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;255;255;255mshape the replacement.\u001b[39m                                                                                       \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[49m     \u001b[1C   \u001b[1C             \r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;2;215;119;87m✻\u001b[39m \u001b[38;2;215;119;87mStewing… \u001b[39m                                                                                                  \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B                                                      \u001b[4C        "]
