[0.961, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[2D\u001b[4B\r\u001b[5A  I'd recommend \u001b[1mA (linear-pipeline-with-router)\u001b[22m. It gives you pluggable routing without the indirection of a \r\u001b[1B  bus,\u001b[1Cand\u001b[1Cthe\u001b[1Cstage\u001b[1Cboundaries\u001b[1Cmake\u001b[1Cdead-letter\u001b[1Chandling\u001b[1Cand\u001b[1Cschema\u001b[1Cvalidation\u001b[1Cexplicit\u001b[1Crather\u001b[1Cthan\r\u001b[1B  cross-cutting. The pipeline is honest about being linear — and if you ever need fan-out, refactoring a     \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Brouter into a bus is a well-understood path.             \u001b[1C                                               \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B                                        \r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136m─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m❯ \u001b[39m\u001b[7m \u001b[27m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136m─────────────"]
