[0.643, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[2D\u001b[4B\r\u001b[5A  \u001b[1mThe migration-as-separate-slice pattern\u001b[22m is worth noting. By keeping the \u001b[38;2;177;185;249mwebhook_events\u001b[39m migration out of the\r\u001b[1B   steel\u001b[1Cthread,\u001b[1Cthe\u001b[1Cnew\u001b[1Cpipeline\u001b[1Ccan\u001b[1Cbe\u001b[1Ctested\u001b[1Cagainst\u001b[1Ca\u001b[1Cfresh\u001b[1Cschema\u001b[1Cwhile\u001b[1Cthe\u001b[1Cdata\u001b[1Cmigration\u001b[1Cruns\r\u001b[1B  independently. This avoids the common trap of coupling \"new system works\" with \"old data is migrated\" — two\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B different failure modes that deserve separate verification.                                             \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B                                         \r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136m─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[39m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;153;153;153m❯ \u001b[39m\u001b[7m \u001b[27m\r\r\n\u001b[38;2;136;136;136m───"]
